{"title_page": "Coronavirus pandemic anti-Muslim riots in India", "text_new": "{{short description|Anti-Muslim conflict in India}}\nThe '''[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in India|coronavirus pandemic]]''' '''anti -illiterate and anti national Muslims riots''' refers to an ongoing series of [[Religious violence|religiously motivated]] riots or [[Lynching|mob attack]]s that are being carried out by the [[Violent extremism|extremist]]s against the [[Muslims]] in India as said by some intelligent peoples it is a riot against Muslims but it's not the truth. But you know there are some tension between society as attacks on corona warriors were reported in Muslim majority region .and it has been said that it will increase if attacks by Muslims began to continue.<ref name=\"Apoorvanand 2020\">{{cite web | author=Apoorvanand | title=How the coronavirus outbreak in India was blamed on Muslims | website=Al Jazeera | date=18 April 2020 | url=https://www.aljazeera.com/indepth/opinion/coronavirus-outbreak-india-blamed-muslims-200418143252362.html | access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> The lynching incidents occurred primarily after [[Tablighi Jamaat]] was held responsible by the officials for [[2020 Tablighi Jamaat coronavirus hotspot in Delhi|spreading covid-19]] in the country.<ref name=\"nytimes\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/12/world/asia/india-coronavirus-muslims-bigotry.html|title=In India, Coronavirus Fans Religious Hatred|first1=Jeffrey|last1=Gettleman|first2=Kai|last2=Schultz|first3=Suhasini|last3=Raj|date=April 12, 2020|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://theintercept.com/2020/04/14/coronavirus-muslims-islamophobia/|title=The Coronavirus Is Empowering Islamophobes \u2014 but Exposing the Idiocy of Islamophobia|first=Mehdi|last=Hasan|date=April 14, 2020}}</ref> Mob cases were reported by the [[news media]] after some people related to the missionary were tested positive for [[pandemic]] of [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]], though infectious disease spread [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|worldwide]] with thousands of deaths since it originated in 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://foreignpolicy.com/2020/03/28/india-delhi-first-came-the-pogroms-now-theres-coronavirus/|title=In Delhi, First Came the Pogroms. Then Came Coronavirus.|first=Yashraj|last=Sharma}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/coronavirus/covid-19-rumours-linked-to-3-attacks-in-delhi-gurgaon-6350696/|title=COVID-19 rumours linked to 3 attacks in Delhi, Gurgaon|date=April 7, 2020}}</ref> The pandemic triggered severe [[Strike (attack)|attack]]s on the minorities, leading violence between the adherents.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/04/12/briefing/coronavirus-india-anti-muslim-attacks.html|title=Anti-Muslim Attacks, Boris Johnson, China's New Cases: Your Monday Briefing|first=Melina|last=Delkic|date=April 12, 2020|via=NYTimes.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2020/04/17/technology/17reuters-health-coronavirus-india-muslims-insight.html|title=In Modi's India, Virus Fallout Inflames Divisions Between Muslims and Hindus|newspaper=The New York Times|date=April 17, 2020}}</ref> An Indian novelist and activist [[Arundhati Roy]] termed the [[sectarian violence]] \"approaching to genocide\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/en/indias-treatment-of-muslims-amid-coronavirus-is-almost-genocidal-activist-arundhati-roy-claims/a-53167812|title=India's treatment of Muslims amid coronavirus is almost 'genocidal,' activist Arundhati Roy claims &#124; DW &#124; 17.04.2020|first=Deutsche|last=Welle (www.dw.com)|website=DW.COM}}</ref><ref name=\"Desk 2020\">{{cite web | last=Desk | first=Web | title=India should protect rights of Muslims amid COVID-19 crisis: OIC - Pakistan | website=The News International | date=19 April 2020 | url=https://www.thenews.com.pk/latest/646709-india-should-protect-muslim-minoritys-rights-amid-covid-19-crisis-islamophobia-oic | access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref>as she wanted to come in lime light she said all these foolish things as she ignored the health ministry's official data and as she dont know that jamatis were responsible in many countries for spreding cpronavirus .It is said that '''#CoronaJihad''' [[hashtag]] has been distributed 300,000 times on [[social media]] amid the violent. But there have been no official sources and may be these are wrong as its been reported by Indian media that the Muslim preacher maulana saad ignored the warnings and was misleading the jamatis and there were reports which confirm that jamatis don't love their nations only but also don't possess humanitarian values as they misbehaved Doctors and nurses. It was Muslim areas where public servants were attacked.\n\n==Background==\nSince the [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] case was detected in India on 30 January 2020, the [[Religious violence in India|religious violence]] sparked among the people from different adherents, especially Hindus accusing [[Minority religion|minorities]] for infecting the citizens of the country, though the [[Government of India]] did not took measures to stop religious activities at the earliest.<ref name=\"RFI 2020\">{{cite web | title=Coronavirus pandemic used to stir-up anti-Muslim prejeudice in India | website=RFI | date=13 April 2020 | url=http://www.rfi.fr/en/international/20200413-coronavirus-pandemic-used-to-stir-up-anti-muslim-prejeudice-in-india | access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> People argued that [[Media of India|Indian news media]] didn't played significantly to stop [[victimisation]] of the Muslims that led some people of the minorities to commit suicide while several others were harassed or lynched at different places.<ref name=\"voa\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.voanews.com/extremism-watch/coronavirus-spread-india-sparks-intolerance-toward-minority-muslims|title=Coronavirus Spread in India Sparks Intolerance Toward Minority Muslims &#124; Voice of America - English|website=www.voanews.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.thewire.in/article/communalism/coronavirus-anti-muslim-propaganda-india|title=The Coronavirus Has Morphed Into an Anti-Muslim Virus|website=The Wire}}</ref> Tablighi Jamaat, a Muslim missionary held several [[Ijtema|congregation]]s in the country, claiming in rise of coronavirus cases before [[2020 coronavirus lockdown in India|lockdown was imposed]] in the country.<ref name=\"Beydoun 2020\">{{cite web | last=Beydoun | first=Khaled A. | title=Between virus and violence: The horror of being Muslim in India | website=alaraby | date=17 April 2020 | url=https://english.alaraby.co.uk/english/comment/2020/4/17/between-virus-and-violence-being-muslim-in-india | access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref> It is said that [[Hindus]] were also actively involved in organising religious debates.<ref name=\"voa\"/>\n\nSome Hindus, including a teenager was also lynched by the mob attackers over not conducted [[COVID-19 testing]] of his two coworkers.<ref name=\"Raj 2020\">{{cite web | last=Raj | first=Dev | title=Teenager lynched for virus alert | website=Telegraph India | date=1 April 2020 | url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/india/bihar-teenager-lynched-for-coronavirus-alert/cid/1760987 | access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Withnall 2020\">{{cite web | last=Withnall | first=Adam | title=Man in India lynched after reporting migrant workers to authorities over coronavirus fears | website=The Independent | date=31 March 2020 | url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/asia/india-coronavirus-migrant-lynching-madhaul-bihar-quarantine-a9438186.html | language=ca | access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Social media controversies==\nThe political leaders, including 25 members of [[Bharatiya Janata Party]] termed the islamic conference or congregation \"#coronaJihad\", \"#CoronaTerrorism\" and \"#CoronaBombsTablighi\" using the hashtags that were subsequently circulated by the [[internet users]] across the social media, including Twitter.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/13/coronavirus-conspiracy-theories-targeting-muslims-spread-in-india|title=Coronavirus conspiracy theories targeting Muslims spread in India|first=Hannah Ellis-Petersen Shaikh Azizur Rahman in|last=Kolkata|newspaper=The Guardian|date=April 13, 2020|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=https://time.com/5815264/coronavirus-india-islamophobia-coronajihad/|title=It Was Already Dangerous To Be Muslim in India. Then Came the Coronavirus|website=Time}}</ref> An Indian politician and former wrestler [[Babita Phogat]] wrote on tweet stating that \"Muslims are bigger problem than even the virus\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-india-52320900|title=India stars under fire for 'anti-Muslim' tweets|work=BBC News|date=April 17, 2020|via=www.bbc.com}}</ref> Her tweet was later criticised by the several people using \"#SupendBabitaPhogat\" [[Twitter]] hashtag.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/babita-phogat-faces-backlash-over-controversial-tweets-on-tablighi-jamaat-1668008-2020-04-17|title=Babita Phogat faces backlash over controversial tweets on Tablighi Jamaat|first1=India Today Web Desk New|last1=DelhiApril 17|first2=2020UPDATED|last2=April 17|first3=2020 15:18|last3=Ist|website=India Today}}</ref> The UAE's [[royal family]] member [[Hend Faisal Al Qassemi]] criticised the anti-Muslim tweets posted by an Indian politician [[Deendayal Upadhyaya]] who allegedly made statements against attendants of congregation held in the country during COVID-19 outbreak.<ref name=\"News18 2020\">{{cite web | title='You'll be Made to Leave': UAE Princess Slams Indian Man for Islamophobic Tweet on Tablighi Jamaat | website=News18 | date=18 April 2020 | url=https://www.news18.com/news/buzz/youll-be-made-to-leave-uae-princess-slams-indian-man-for-islamophobic-tweet-on-tablighi-jamaat-2582657.html | access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Safoora Safoora Safoora 2020\">{{cite web | title=UAE Princess takes a strong stand against racist comment | website=The Siasat Daily | date=17 April 2020 | url=https://www.siasat.com/uae-princess-takes-strong-stand-against-racist-comment-1875200/ | access-date=18 April 2020}}</ref> Some Indian employees working with Dubai-based private companies suffered [[termination of employment]] for allegedly sharing coronavirus-violence related posts on social media.<ref name=\"PTI 2020\">{{cite web | author=PTI | title=Another Indian expat in UAE sacked over Islamophobic post | website=The Hindu | date=13 April 2020 | url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/another-indian-expat-in-uae-sacked-for-islamophobic-post/article31328980.ece | access-date=19 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Lynching deaths in India]]\n[[Category:Hinduism-related controversies]]\n[[Category:Hinduism-motivated violence in India]]\n[[Category:2020 crimes in India]]\n[[Category:Religiously motivated violence in India]]\n[[Category:Anti-Muslim violence in India]]\n[[Category:September 2020 events in Asia]]\n[[Category:Murder in India]]\n[[Category:2020 murders in Asia]]\n[[Category:2020s murders in India]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Anti-Muslim conflict in India}}\n{{Infobox civilian attack\n| title      = Coronavirus pandemic anti-Muslim riots in India\n| image      = \n| caption    = \n| map = India states and union territories map.svg\n| map_caption = A map showing the states and union territories of India, including [[Delhi]], [[Bihar]] and [[Uttar Pradesh]]\n| location   = India\n| coordinates = \n| target     = [[Muslim]]s<ref name=\"nytimes\"/>\n| date       = 2020\n| time       = \n| timezone   = \n| type       =  [[Lynching]], [[Harassment]]\n| fatalities = \n| injuries   = \n| perps      = [[Hindu nationalism|Hindu nationalist]]s <ref name=\"Qantara.de - Dialogue with the Islamic World\">{{cite web | title=Coronavirus in India: Muslims as scapegoats | website=Qantara.de - 